-- monthly_subscription_metrics.sql
WITH billing_deduped AS (
  SELECT DISTINCT ON (subscription_id, event_month)
    subscription_id,
    event_month,
    amount
  FROM billing_events
  ORDER BY subscription_id, event_month, event_id
),
subscription_details AS (
  SELECT
    DATE_TRUNC('month', COALESCE(b.event_month, s.started_at))::DATE AS month,
    COALESCE(p.tier, 'Unknown') AS tier,
    COALESCE(c.industry, 'Unknown') AS industry,
    s.subscription_id,
    u.user_id,
    b.amount
  FROM subscriptions s
  LEFT JOIN billing_deduped b ON s.subscription_id = b.subscription_id
  LEFT JOIN plans p ON s.plan_id = p.plan_id
  LEFT JOIN users u ON s.user_id = u.user_id
  LEFT JOIN companies c ON u.company_id = c.company_id
  WHERE s.status = 'active'
    OR (b.event_month IS NOT NULL AND b.event_month >= DATE_TRUNC('month', s.started_at)::DATE)
    OR (s.ended_at IS NULL)
)
SELECT
  month,
  tier,
  industry,
  COUNT(DISTINCT subscription_id) AS active_subscriptions,
  COALESCE(SUM(amount), 0) AS total_mrr,
  COUNT(DISTINCT user_id) AS unique_users
FROM subscription_details
WHERE month IS NOT NULL
GROUP BY month, tier, industry
ORDER BY month DESC, tier, industry;
